- [Documentation Standards](./documentation-standards.mdc) - Technical documentation structure, formatting, and maintenance guidelines, including AI standards like this document

## 4. Domain reference (SST)

- **Normative source of truth**: [`.sst-agent-document.md`](../../.sst-agent-document.md)
  (repo root) documents the SST domain knowledge this backend implements: the
  PHVA cycle, Colombian regulations (Decreto 1072 de 2015, Resolución 312 de
  2019, GTC 45:2012), risk-level calculation (`NR = NP × NC`), the hierarchy of
  controls, and agent-specific normative rules.
- Any business rule, domain model, validation, or endpoint touching SST
  concepts (hazards, risks, audits, minimum standards, controls) must be
  traceable to that document. When planning or implementing a ticket, read it
  before inventing domain behavior; if the ticket contradicts it, flag the
  conflict instead of guessing.


